value.value: A cancer finding in the TNM system that is not specifically identified as a clinical, pathologic, recurrent (retreatment), or autopsy classification using an accepted prefix in accordance with TNM classification guidelines. Though the 6th Edition of the AJCC Cancer Staging Manual indicates that unspecified TNM staging descriptors may be considered synonymous with the corresponding fully specified clinical category, such omission may lead to ambiguity in meaning, and in practice unqualified descriptors are frequently used with other intended meanings.  The generic TNM concepts in the NCI Thesaurus are intended to explicitly reflect this lack of specification.

A neoplasm that arises from the hilar region of lung and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.
TNM staging performed for recurrent cancer.
TNM staging performed with access to clinical information only.
TNM staging performed on autopsy.

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of a specific cancer, following the rules of the TNM classification system as they pertain to evaluating distant metastases.

label.value: Prostate Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of prostate cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

A neoplastic process characterized by a diffuse poorly circumscribed overgrowth of adipose tissue in the breast and cervical areas, and an accumulation of visceral fat.  It is associated with antiretroviral therapy.  Clinical presentation includes hyperlipidemia, insulin resistance, and fat atrophy of the face and limbs.
An epoxide compound with potential antineoplastic alkylating activity. Etoglucid is able to crosslink DNA via its epoxide group, resulting in disruption of DNA function and cell cycle arrest.
A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm involving any part of the digestive system.
A condition in which a finger or toe is larger than normal size secondary to excessive growth of the anatomical structures or abnormal accumulation of substances.

value.value: A measure of the variability in a sample or population. It is calculated as the mean squared deviation (MSD) of the individual values from their common mean. In calculating the MSD, the divisor n is commonly used for a population variance and the divisor n-1 for a sample variance.
Any of the 99 numbered points that divide an ordered set of scores into 100 parts each of which contains one-hundredth of the total.

label.value: Stage 0 Small Intestinal Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)
Division of a distribution into equal, ordered subgroups; a set of 'cut points' that divide a sample of data into groups containing (as far as possible) equal numbers of observations.
A time period, or other type of interval, during which something may be achieved, obtained or observed.
A constant number that serves as a measure of some property or characteristic.
